  "body": "The quo2 input component currently does not adapt to the content inside the input in terms of changing its height when the content exceeds available space in one line.\r\n\r\nThis behaviour is required and observed in at least 2 places in the app\r\n- Adding a new contact \r\n- Entering scan sync code\r\n\r\nExisting Quo2 component screenshot : \r\n\r\n<img width=\"418\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-08-03 at 2 34 06 PM\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/64726664/879a14db-ccb5-4c06-ae45-29e6919a90a1\">\r\n\r\nExpected behaviour : \r\n<img width=\"406\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-08-03 at 2 35 16 PM\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/64726664/832f27ee-3f62-44f6-b9d2-f5197edc8903\">\r\n\r\n\r\nOnce this change has been done, replace the usage of custom input implementations in the following places : \r\n- Adding a new contact \r\n- Entering scan sync code\r\n- Any other place you may discover\r\n\r\nDesign system reference : https://www.figma.com/file/WQZcp6S0EnzxdTL4taoKDv/Design-System-for-Mobile?type=design&node-id=26363-231238&mode=design&t=YJFoohnCKW9L6Un4-0\r\n\r\nAn update by @ulisesmac : The input component does have multiline support but it was impacted as a result of the react native upgrade. So currently the input expands but only upto 2 lines maximum. \r\nThe expected result is to ensure that that the multiline variant of input component expands the height to accommodate whatever is the size of the content\r\n",
